commitResults.messageBody:
Memory class stores tasks in a ArrayList, this is reset every time
the chatbot is ran, does not allow user to store their tasks
for later.

Tasks are now also stored in an external file to allow access
across different runs of the chatbot.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Deadline Class to store date and time as java.time.LocalDate
commitResults.messageBody:
Deadline class used to take in and store date as String

Now it takes in date and time in the ISO-8601 format

commitResults.messageTitle: Split Memory class into Storage and TaskList class, add Ui class
commitResults.messageBody:
Memory class was in charge of both manupilating the stored tasks as well as saving the tasks to external file.

Now storage class handles the saving and reading of data from the external file.
TaskLists handles the manipulation, including adding, removing and marking etc.
Ui handles all interaction with user.

Add parser class and Command classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Ui class handled parsing user input, deciding what to do with
user input, and also returning String messages to inform the user.

Parsing of user input and decision marking has been extracted and
placed in their own classes for better control.

Parser class takes in user input and returns the appropriate
command object

All command classes extends from abstract class Command,
which allows polymorphism when dealing with the command returned
by Parser.

Abstracted out methods from parse method in Parser class.
Previously, parse method was too long and had weak SLAP,
processing the user input has now been abstracted out into multiple
other methods to maintain good SLAP.

Made the happy path prominent in Tasklist.
Previously, methods in tasklist class handle the main path first,
and checked for unusual cases later.
Now, methods check for unusual conditions immediately and keeps
the main path un-indented

Edit default branch in loadfromfile method in storage
to throw an error.
